# Better collapse test
# A 2-ring hexagonal patch where the center vertex is split into two (1 and 2).
# The distance between 1 and 2 is 0.3, while all other edges are roughly 1.0.
# When 1 and 2 collapse to (0,0,0), the new edge lengths to the 1-ring will be exactly 1.0, 
# which is safely below the l_max threshold (~1.33), allowing the collapse to succeed.

# Center split vertices (Edge length = 0.3)
v -0.15 0.0 0.0
v  0.15 0.0 0.0

# Ring 1 (Radius 1.0 from center)
v  1.0  0.0 0.0
v  0.5  0.866025 0.0
v -0.5  0.866025 0.0
v -1.0  0.0 0.0
v -0.5 -0.866025 0.0
v  0.5 -0.866025 0.0

# Ring 2 (Radius 2.0 from center)
v  2.0  0.0 0.0
v  1.5  0.866025 0.0
v  1.0  1.73205 0.0
v  0.0  1.73205 0.0
v -1.0  1.73205 0.0
v -1.5  0.866025 0.0
v -2.0  0.0 0.0
v -1.5 -0.866025 0.0
v -1.0 -1.73205 0.0
v  0.0 -1.73205 0.0
v  1.0 -1.73205 0.0
v  1.5 -0.866025 0.0

# Faces Ring 1 (Center)
f 2 3 4
f 1 2 4
f 1 4 5
f 1 5 6
f 1 6 7
f 1 7 2
f 2 7 8
f 2 8 3

# Faces Ring 2
f 3 9 10
f 3 10 4
f 4 10 11
f 4 11 12
f 4 12 5
f 5 12 13
f 5 13 14
f 5 14 6
f 6 14 15
f 6 15 16
f 6 16 7
f 7 16 17
f 7 17 18
f 7 18 8
f 8 18 19
f 8 19 20
f 8 20 3
f 3 20 9